nt` and `ConditionalOnAvailableEndpoint`, which might default to enabled if `spring-boot-actuator` is there. It makes me curious about the actual sources of this information. Perhaps I could use `javap` to explore auto-configurations further. It's all kind of technical, but it feels important to get it right!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1tzYwUvSHFUDtBrgxMU8nJXh|fc_0cf657c4fedd7778016a3eee8e76f88195895d21258136981a", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-liquibase/4.1.0/build/jacoco/effective/spring_boot_liquibase_4_1_0_jar -v org.springframework.boot.liquibase.autoconfigure.LiquibaseEndpointAutoConfiguration | grep -A80 'RuntimeVisibleAnnotations'", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3709, "output": 1174, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33555, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782509173051, "responseId": "resp_0cf657c4fedd7778016a3eee75823081958362f68b6ca74dd6"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_1tzYwUvSHFUDtBrgxMU8nJXh|fc_0cf657c4fedd7778016a3eee8e76f88195895d21258136981a", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "  #27 = Utf8               RuntimeVisibleAnnotations\n  #28 = Utf8               Lorg/springframework/context/annotation/Bean;\n  #29 = Utf8               Lorg/springframework/boot/autoconfigure/condition/ConditionalOnBean;\n  #30 = Utf8               value\n  #31 = Utf8               Lliquibase/integration/spring/SpringLiquibase;\n  #32 = Utf8               Lorg/springframework/boot/autoconfigure/condition/ConditionalOnMissingBean;\n  #33 = Utf8               preventDataSourceCloseBeanPostProcessor\n  #34 = Utf8               ()Lorg/springframework/beans/factory/config/BeanPostProcessor;\n  #35 = Utf8               SourceFile\n  #36 = Utf8               Liqu